snippet: As they sit in a four-way tie atop the A.F.C. East, the Jets are hoping a strong performance Sunday against rival New England will define the remainder of the season.
abstract: New York Jets are preparing to face rival New England Patriots; both teams stand at 3-3, and are part of a four-team tie for first in AFC East.
lead_paragraph: As they sit in a four-way tie atop the A.F.C. East, the Jets are hoping a strong performance Sunday against rival New England will define the remainder of the season.

headline.seo: Jets Welcome Renewal of Rivalry With Patriots
headline.main: Jets Welcome Renewal of Rivalry With Patriots
headline.print_headline: Jets Eager to Renew Acquaintances With Patriots, Their Rivals at .500
